Path: This week in Nu #21
Content:
thegedge and andrasio have been hard at work at improving how externals are spawned and handled inside of the pipeline builder (
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/1231] #1231
, 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/1230] #1230
, 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/1211] #1211
, 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/1182] #1182
)
jonathandturner has begun commenting the codebase (
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/1229] #1229
, 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/1228] #1228
, 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/1225] #1225
)
jonathandturner also improved 
``ls``
 to be simpler (
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/1195] #1195
, 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/1194] #1194
, 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/1192] #1192
)
koenaad added support for sending more value types as $it to externals (
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/1218] #1218
, 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/1220] #1220
, 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/1210] #1210
)
jonathandturner and andrasio improved testing (
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/1200] #1200
, 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/1198] #1198
)
andrasio extended 
``pick``
 to allow column paths and not just column names (
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/1191] #1191
) and improved 
``get``
 errors (
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/1185] #1185
)
